in a recent msg, paul@kuhub.cc.ukans.edu wrote:
>I'd hope that cellular phone designers would not make mobile terminals
>that constantly communicate with the cell base part of the system when
>a car's electrical circuits are turned on, but only when the system
>is "off the hook" (preparing to make a phone call).

Seems to me that in order to get incoming calls, a cellphone has to respond
to system-wide pages by sending out a response that will tell the system
which cell it's in, and how to route the incoming call. I don't think the
system is more sophisticated than that, though.
-Steve

